  "texts": [
    "-What common challenges and opportunities emerge from the literature regarding AI's contribution to resilience?",
    "Our review of 385 academic papers reveals significant trends in AI-driven resilience research.",
    "A majority (64.4%) of studies focus on adaptation, addressing challenges such as climate forecasting, risk assessment, and infrastructure resilience.",
    "Only 16% emphasize mitigation, while 19.4% integrate both approaches, underscoring the need for stronger AI contributions to emissions reduction strategies.",
    "In terms of AI methodologies, Classical Machine Learning/General ML dominate the field, appearing in 51.4% of studies, followed by Deep Learning (22.3%), and Traditional Machine Learning & Ensemble Models (8.3%) and Natural Language Processing & Text Mining (2.3%)."
  ],
